[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: GHOST TextForge and RagLog Logging Requirements
UID: GHOST-LOG
VERSION: 0.1-draft
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text
  AUTO_LEVELS: On
  NODE_IN_TOC: True

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 1. Purpose

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Defines the TextForge/RagLog functional logging subsystem and its observability role, including TextForge facade, TextSink base, FileSink, CliSink, GUISink, RagLog public functions, sink routing, type/sensitivity filtering, developer diagnostics, runtime log display, and future hardening.
<<<

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 2. Scope and Boundary

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-LOG-ROOT
TITLE: GHOST TextForge and RagLog Logging Scope
STATEMENT: >>>
This file is a draft child requirement file in the GHOST StrictDoc requirement tree.

It defines ownership, scope, and placeholder headings for this capability area. Detailed atomic requirements shall be migrated here from legacy requirements, implementation status, architecture notes, UML files, and code evidence after human approval.

This file shall not duplicate detailed requirements owned by sibling files.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-QGO-ROOT

